The paper presents a novel method for adjusting hyper-parameters in Deep Learning algorithms, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The method is specifically designed for Deep Learning algorithms used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the method involves an external agent-observer that monitors the performance of the DL algorithm, which can be seen as a control system (cs.SY) for the DL algorithm. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
